**About the Team**


We are **Quadcode**, a fintech company excelling in financial brokerage activities and delivering advanced financial products to our global clientele. Our flagship product, an internal trading platform, is offered as a Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) solution to other brokers.


We are looking for an experienced and dynamic **Business** **Development Manager** **(IB B2B)** to join our QCM team.


QCM is a certified broker with its own trading platform with all top assets: from CFD on stocks to commodities, in more than 1000 markets at the same time. We're creating a new way of trading with our platform that was designed and created by traders with a powerful and modern desktop trading terminal as a standalone application. We understand how to ease your experience of trading and help you to get more with risk management tools, hedging models, flexible leverages, graphics, etc.


Currently, we are ready to launch our IB offer for the LATAM market. We're looking for a proactive leader who can help us to grow above our plans.



As a BDM you will work on the strategy launch of the IB direction in the LATAM market, attract new partners, and build a team.



You will interact with a diverse group of individuals within the organization, including sales representatives, marketing and affiliate professionals, product managers, and customer support specialists. The candidate needs to be able to communicate effectively with individuals from different teams and backgrounds to ensure the success of their role.


Since this is a new direction for us, you will have the opportunity to implement your initiatives, conduct experiments, and influence decision-making. In the future, there is potential for growth to Head of IB, overseeing not only the LATAM market but also other locations.



**Tasks in the role**



* Developing the strategy for launching IB in the LATAM market;
* Acquiring new IB partners;
* Onboarding IB partners;
* Creating offers for IB;
* Managing the team of IB (KPI, mentoring);
* Cultivating strong business relationships with key decision-makers;
* Managing unit economics.


**Requirements**


* Affiliate / IB experience of at least 1 year;
* B2B sales experience;
* Flexible mindset - you have to start with operational work;
* Management skills with unit-economic understanding;
* Client's portfolio you can start with;
* Located in LATAM;
* Fluency in Spanish/Portuguese and English.


**We offer**


* Full-time remote work as a Service Provider;
* Opportunity to become a PO of the whole department/Head of IB;
* Market salary;
* A wide range of tools to get started with IB: RevShare/Spread Share/CPA.



Currently, over 700 employees and service providers are stationed across its seven global offices located in the UK, Gibraltar, the UAE, the Bahamas, Australia, and the headquarters in Cyprus. By broadening its international presence, Quadcode not only offers a remote or hybrid work model but also presents a myriad of intriguing tasks and challenges for professionals like developers, market research analysts, and PR marketing specialists, among others.


Join us today, and let's shape the future of fintech together!


***Note:*** *All applications will be treated with strict confidence. We thank all applicants for their interest, however, only those candidates selected for interviews will be contacted.*  



*#LI-DG1 #LI-Remote*

**Soft dB – Acoustics & Vibration Experts**, the largest firm in Canada specializing in acoustics and vibration, is seeking an experienced **Business Development Manager** for our Monitoring division. With over 25 years in the industry, we are known worldwide for our cutting-edge acoustical and vibration engineering expertise (consulting, monitoring, noise control) and sound masking technology.

Our monitoring division is growing rapidly and we are looking for someone to accelerate the development of our activities in vibro-acoustic monitoring. By joining us, you will have the opportunity to actively contribute to the success of the most advanced monitoring solution on the market!

The position is based in Mississauga, Ontario, our latest office. Join our dynamic company and take your career to the next level!

**Soft dB Monitoring Solution:**

Our monitoring system allows real-time, 24/7 monitoring of noise and vibration levels across various outdoor sites (e.g., industrial, construction sites, quarries and sand pits, mining operations, and more). Our monitoring stations communicate with our web platform and allows site managers to be notified instantly when there are risks of exceeding their noise and vibration limits. They are thus able to ensure the continuous compliance of their sites with current environmental standards and make informed decisions regarding their operations (e.g. blasting, excavation, crushing, screening, etc.).

**RESPONSIBILITIES:**

Under the supervision of the director of the monitoring division, the responsibilities of the business development manager will be:

* Represent Soft dB with an impeccable attitude that is positive, productive, professional, and geared toward genuine customer satisfaction;
* Establish business development objectives with Soft dB’s management team and deploy all available resources to meet and exceed the objectives;
* Reach out and follow up with potential customers;
* Build business relationships with current and potential customers;
* Present and demonstrate the monitoring solution;
* Assure the link between the customers and the technical team;
* Prepare proposals in collaboration with the team;
* Maintain Soft dB’s customer database (CRM) with relevant customers and potential customer information.

**REQUIREMENTS:**

· 5 to 10 years in sales or business development with a strong track record in one or more of the following sectors:

* Monitoring;
* Construction;
* Facilities project management.

· Knowledge of the Toronto market;

· Computer proficiency to produce documents in MS Word, Excel, and PowerPoint;

· Experience in database/sales tool management (CRM);

· A driver’s licence.

**PERSONNAL SKILLS:**

* Entrepreneurial mindset;
* Result oriented;
* Excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
* Solid critical thinking and organisational skills;
* Enthusiastic and self-motivated;
* Good writing skills;
* Self-starter and able to interact with people at all levels;
* Knowledge of acoustics and vibrations (an asset);
* Knowledge of French language (an asset);

**GENERAL CONDITIONS & WHY JOIN US:**

* Full time, permanent;
* Flexible schedule: 40 hours/week;
* Competitive salary commensurate with experience;
* Generous commission plan based on results obtained;
* Employer contribution to employee RRSP;
* Hybrid: From home and from our office in Mississauga, ON (320 Matheson Blvd W Suite # 107, Mississauga, ON L5R 3R1);
* Telemedicine/support program and Employee Assistance Program (EAP);
* Lump sum for home office (after 3 months);
* Stimulating work environment with passionate teams (and fun social activities!);
* Offices closed between Christmas and New Year's.

If you're looking for a role where you can make a real impact and help shape the future of a dynamic and rapidly growing company, we want to hear from you!

